      "writtenOn": "2018-03-26T16:56:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "didn\u0027t you also planned to include subject line?\n\nstepping back, i am thinking of simplifying this. WDYT about separate template files instead of a single text proto files with a bunch of embedded HTML files? I think it would be simpler for users. The file structure could be \n\nluci-notify/\n  email-templates/\n    default.template\n    foo.template\n    mysteps.template\n\nthe name of the file defines the template name. A file can include another template as\n  \n  {{template \"mysteps\" .Build.Steps}}\n  \nWe could define its format as: one or more headers, each on its own line; then a blank line, then the body. A header format matches HTTP headers, so e.g. \"Subject: [Build Status] Builder {{ .Builder }} on]{{ .Status }}\"\n\nThe parsing of the text as headers-and-body takes place AFTER the template is rendered, so that allows the subject line to be a template.",
      "revId": "d2b6ed8db1683f6656c75d7881e926bcca338f73",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
